      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOST HIS BEANS (2) loves racing here on his home circuit winning five from five including three over this sprint journey. Gets the services of gun hoop Maloney in the irons and draws favourably from the inside marble. Sure to be right there at the business end. PROVANCE (3) was a touch plain last time out but the three runs prior were good enough for a race of this nature. Capable of bouncing right back. ADMITTED (4) got the job done over this course and distance at the latest outing and Thompson stays in the saddle. Can go back-to-back. CHALICE WELL (7) goes well for rider Brooker who has three wins and a placing from seven rides. Strips fitter now and is capable of sharp improvement. THELWELL (1) best of the rest while fresh.",
